(1, '2012-11-05 19:27:46', 'Maria Foo', 'mariafoo@iinet.net.au', '27-11-1992', 'Canberra-Australia', 'marialourdesmadalena', 1, 'st_s1_c1', 'weekly', '2010 - Graduated High School\n2011 - Entered ANU (B. Actuarial/B. Finance) (expected grad date 2014)', 'AIESEC, University, Polycademy...', 'None', 'I want to build this: http://www.gaffta.org/2012/08/29/the-art-of-data-visualization-webgl-and-three-js-qa-with-michael-chang/\n\nBut for AIESEC EPs.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(3, '2012-11-23 13:44:47', 'Nicky Hughes', 'niggles2000@hotmail.com', '', '', 'nicky.hughes1984', 0, 'st_s1_c1,st_s1_c2,ex_t1', '', '', '', '', 'Right now it would mean everything to me to be accepted into Polycademy. I am in the process of a career change, having worked as an architect for the last four years. But now, I am returning to my original passion that I developed in my teens which is coding and digital design.  I also am constantly attempting to come up with ideas for a Startup, I just need to come up with just the right idea and be able to build it with the skills I learn at Polycademy.\n\nI have an eclectic mix of interests and skills - I topped my school in English and Visual Arts, and also finished in the top five in both Extension Mathematics and Software Design and Development. At university I graduated with a Bachelor of Architecture (Hons I), but in my first design degree I majored in digital media in which I studied web design and 3D animation. As a Revit user, Iâ€™ve built parametric families in Revit, making use of my programming knowledge in the architectural field. I also enjoy writing, dragon-boating and training for half-marathons.\n\nI am in the process of  setting up a web page as an ongoing project to practice and showcase my web design skills. I ultimately want to turn this into a web development business,  but at this point I need to learn so many elements that feed into web development - the full stack. I would ultimately love to design websites and apps for organisations and groups under my own studio name, but I would need to hone my skills working for a development company first.  \n\nI am also very interested in the Code for Australia program. I volunteered for three months in 2006 in Peru with an NGO working on development projects in remote communities, and I am interested in social issues and the idea of using my skills to help others. Code for Australia is something I would be interested in becoming involved with once I have the skills and the means to do so.\n\nI have the creativity, the drive, the determination - all I need is the web development skills to be able to create something special. If given this incredible opportunity, the only one of its kind in Australia, I would make the most of every minute of the course and do everything within my power to be successful.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(6, '2012-11-30 00:29:29', 'Jashwanth Reddy', 'jashwanthreddy12@gmail.com', '', '', 'jashwanth12', 0, 'ex_t1', '', '', '', '', 'My own web page ,PHP,JavaScript,HTML,CSS etc...  excellent web skills', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(7, '2012-12-13 12:26:14', 'Phuong Trinh', 'phuonglan.trinh91@gmail.com', '11-01-1991', 'Canberra, Australia', 'ngua_con_cao_co', 0, 'ex_t1', 'upfront', 'University', 'University', 'No', 'I have not yet had any idea, but hopefully through Polycademy, I can get out sth and develop my ideas. Cheers :D :D :D', 'Friends', '', '+61412078661', 1, 1, 1),
(8, '2012-12-15 13:34:14', 'Jackson GotheSnape', 'jacksongs@gmail.com', '', '', 'jgothesnape', 0, 'ex_t1', '', '', '', '', 'I''d like to learn more about security and building robust production-grade apps, as well as front-end design and development.\n\nI''ve got a fantasy league app that needs polishing before I launch it publicly, and some other ideas around online video.\n\n(PS: Let me put a hyphen in the last name field!)', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(9, '2012-12-16 21:53:35', 'Peta Bellamy', 'petabellamy@gmail.com', '', '', 'peta.bellamy', 0, 'st_s2_c1,st_s2_c2,ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'Something awesome!', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(10, '2012-12-18 16:52:53', 'joe lemura', 'joe@lemura.com.au', '', '', 'jlemura', 0, 'st_s1_c1,st_s2_c1', '', '', '', '', 'Be able to further develop my data visualization idea combining original ideas and Gov 2.0 open data.\nAlso to be uber awesome.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(11, '2012-12-21 02:32:56', 'John Whitcombe', 'john@whitcombefamily.org', '', '', 'whitcombej2', 0, 'st_s1_c1,st_s1_c2', '', '', '', '', 'I''d like to build a student attendance tracking and performance monitoring solution that schools and educators could use free of charge to engage parents, legislators and the broader community in achieving educational excellence for all. Instead of basing an assessment of a school''s achievement on NAPLAN results, this system would look to assess each student''s individual educational journey on a holistic level using test results, truancy and other engagement indicators to support teachers and administrators in proactive support at times of difficulty.\n\nI''ve worked in education for five years both in pastoral roles (at colleges) and as a tutor and believe that while the Khan academy and other online tools are wonderful - the role of the teacher and the educator in driving a child to succeed is still very much present. Educators and schools shouldn''t have to pay anything to communicate and engage more effectively with their students on a holistic level through technology and I''d like to start development of a solution that uses data to address individual needs rather than to provide data for the financing arrangements of bureaucrats.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(12, '2012-12-23 17:39:13', 'Kai Faust', 'kai@kyniko.com', '', '', 'kaitunes', 0, 'st_s1_c1', '', '', '', '', 'I want to build a powerful and interactive web-based FTP client. No company has created a remarkable FTP web app (yet): I want to be the first to utilize both design (a talent I already have) with functionality (a talent that I wish to learn in this 21 week course). I am sufficient at HTML/CSS, and have an intermediate familiarity with Python.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(13, '2012-12-24 12:52:33', 'Ash Newport', 'ashnewport23@gmail.com', '23-03-1989', 'Chisholm ACT, Australia', 'chickensoup64', 0, 'ex_t1', 'upfront', 'A couple of web certifications at Diploma and below, but nothing fancy. I work with websites on a daily basis.', 'Full time job during day hours. Uni studies (taking a break while attending Polycademy)', 'None', 'I''d like to be able to build anything really. The hands on of the course with topics relevant to industry seems interesting and working on something start to finish is awesome. Being able to use this education in the real world is what I''m hoping for.', 'I think it was an email promoting your offerings.', '', '+61419217650', 1, 1, 1),
(14, '2012-12-29 11:34:11', 'Matthew Maher', 'matthew.alexander.maher@gmail.com', '19-10-1986', 'Mildura VIC, Australia', 'ell0motto', 0, 'ex_t1', 'upfront', 'Year 12. Continuously employed since 18. Cert 4 in IT Diploma in Accounting Diploma in Financial Planning', 'Nil', 'Basic understanding of HTML, Java &amp; Python', 'Electronically enhanced POS system with integrated mobile app aimed to add value to food courts, fast food outlets &amp; airports.', 'Response to Blog', '', '+61409953133', 1, 1, 1),
(15, '2013-01-01 23:42:46', 'Joseph Hong', 'hzh.joseph@gmail.com', '', '', 'neo.jhzh', 0, 'st_s1_c2', '', '', '', '', 'Gamified online reviewing/commentary sites/mobile app that can be used by foodies and regular eater to certify their experience', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(17, '2013-01-08 23:35:02', 'Tony COMMISSO', 'Tony@commisso.com.au', '', '', 'Tony.commisso', 0, 'st_s2_c1', '', '', '', '', 'Currently a non tech cofounder and want to be more hands on. Front end ideas abound. We are developing for appointment based businesses.', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(18, '2013-01-17 09:21:00', 'Joshua Yesberg', 'joshua.yesberg@act.gov.au', '', '', 'I don''t has one', 0, 'st_s1_c1', '', '', '', '', 'Not 100% sure yet, I''ve got a few ideas, just need to know how complex they would be to develop first!', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(19, '2013-01-30 17:36:11', 'Patrick Moody', 'patrick.n.moody@gmail.com', '', '', 'patrick.n.moody', 0, 'ex_t1,ex_t2,ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'I already have a profitable MVP (http://themematcher.com) which has been live for ~6 months. I want to make the leap from ''jack of all trades'' to competent web dev so I can improve my product and become a professional developer!', 'Via lists of bootcamps people had compiled on stackoverflow, hacker news, and most recently http://www.bootcamps.in/', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(20, '2013-02-05 23:21:02', 'Tim Wee', 'timwee999@gmail.com', '18-11-1989', 'Canberra - Australia', 'timwee999', 0, 'ex_t1', 'weekly', 'Bachelor of Actuarial Studies, 2011', 'Working full time at ActewAGL, Studying for Part II of Actuarial qualifications', 'None', 'Chess interface', 'Friend recommendation', '', '+61430093820', 1, 1, 1),
(21, '2013-02-06 12:18:21', 'Zafer Celaloglu', 'zafer.celaloglu@gmail.com', '', '', 'zfr_asfd', 0, 'ex_t2,ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'I want to design powerful and stylish website.', 'I saw site link of the Polycademy from discussion page of the Codecademy.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(22, '2013-03-08 10:23:08', 'Vi Nguyen', 'avj.nguyen@gmail.com', '', '', 'examsuccess', 0, 'ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'Site that enables delivery of accounting services in an easy way involving advice being given for fixed fee.\nLike freelancer.com for accountants and financial advisers only.', 'A comment you posted up on a Sydney dev bootcamp article online.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(23, '2013-04-12 05:04:36', 'Gael Rivaud', 'gael.rivaud@greetest.com', '', '', 'gael1305', 0, 'ex_t2', '', '', '', '', 'I created my own company, Greetest. It is a visual dashboard built on Ruby on rails and MongoDB.\n\nGreetest is the first private social network for teams to discover and monitor real-time news together :\n\n- TIMETABLE: discover &amp; choose when to receive the right information at the right time\n=&amp;gt; Save time and efforts\n\n- Share &amp; monitor the same feeds together to communicate instantly\n=&amp;gt; Instant &amp; easy collaboration\n\n- Organize your network &amp; favorites by interests\n=&amp;gt; Clear &amp; optimal organization\n\nLive demo : http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SLeLKsKpd9I', 'I heard about similar programs in the US and I was looking for a program. So I search for a similar program on F6s and stumbled upon Polycademy.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(24, '2013-04-12 18:42:28', 'Amanda Jones', 'kensumption@gmail.com', '', '', 'kenversations', 0, 'ex_t2', '', '', '', '', 'Hello Roger - As discussed previously', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(25, '2013-04-17 15:06:54', 'Haitham Talab', 'haithamtalab@mail.com', '', '', 'haitham.talab1', 0, 'ex_t2,ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'general App development as well as Web development', 'online, through mail.com news interview with dev bootcamp.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(26, '2013-06-03 18:42:32', 'Kevin Myron', 'kdmyron@gmail.com', '', '', 'kdmyron', 0, 'ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'I am recently graduated high school student from the United States whom cannot attend University due to finances. However, I am an aspiring web developer, and have been actively designing my own curriculum in web development through self-learning and building. In fact, I just attended my first hackathon in Seattle, Washington last weekend. \nThrough various resources such as MIT''s OpenCourseWare (http://ocw.mit.edu/index.htm) and Codeacademy (codeacademy.com), I have learned a wealth (and am still actively learning) of knowledge about building websites and coding the back-end. From designing and writing a game in Javascript at that hackathon (http://ischaaf.com/roshki/examples/roshki.html) to Ruby on Rails, I am definitely hooked. However, I believe that personally, I need the structure and environment that Polycademy offers in order to truly unlock my potential.\nI would love to get involved with your Code for Australia project, and experience the culture of another country. As far as projects go, when accepted to Polycademy, I would build an interface that allows for the public to track common imports/exports through Australia and the world, and see where their products come from. I have searched data.gov.au and found a few databases that could come in handy for this (such as http://data.gov.au/dataset/international-trade-in-goods-and-services-australia-apr-2011/). With my experience in database management through SQL and SAS (one of the most flexible and powerful analyzing/processing tools in the market to the date) I believe I could build something quite incredible. \nTo close, I believe that the best thing Polycademy can offer me is the training as an entrepreneur-connecting with people, selling yourself, and innovating. I recently hacked my way into a TEDx conference (read about my experience on the blog on my website- www.KevinMyron.com) where I experienced the rush of pitching your own &quot;story&quot; and learning that of others. It truly is amazing. \nI believe I will bring a lot to the class, and that the class can do wonders for me. Not to mention I would love to be within the first generation of coding for Australia. I have a daunting task ahead of me in proving myself without a formal college degree. Yet I believe that knowledge and experience is not exclusive to a university; it is universal. Learning never stops, as long as you always pursue it.\n-Kevin Myron,\nwww.KevinMyron.com', 'I heard about Polycademy from the link provided under &quot;resources&quot; on Uncollege.org. I have been a fan of Dale Stephen''s work, and actually met him at the TEDx event (read about it on my website- KevinMyron.com) where he encouraged me to pursue programming. Therefore, I decided to follow and apply.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(27, '2013-06-12 02:56:04', 'Tatiana Christian', 'MsChristian88@gmail.com', '', '', 'Tigeress215', 0, 'ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'I want to build a game! I love gaming, and since I''ve been using my ipad a lot more, mobile games (that I enjoy!) are few and far between! My goal is to create a RPG (similar to Final Fantasy but on a smaller scale). The character would collect a few items, fight some bad guys.', 'I found a Quora page listing all the different types of coding bootcamps available.', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(28, '2013-06-21 04:50:51', 'Mustafa Sharar', 'mustafa@sharara.co.uk', '', '', 'mhas161', 0, 'ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'Platform that would allow a unified interface to administer popular CMS platforms. \nThis platform should reduce the time and effort for people or companies who use multiple CMS platform and give them the power to push and manage content and users on these platforms.', 'Google!', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(29, '2013-08-19 21:15:59', 'maddali siddharth', 'siddharthmaddali@gmail.com', '', '', 'siddu2382', 0, 'ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'An online music learning platform targeted towards the Indian market . I would like to get started on this project with the technical skills that i will acquire at Polycademy which will get me a better job at the least!', 'www.quora.com, i was looking for short but intensive programming boot camps for newbies to start coding their venture themselves!', '', '', 0, 0, 0),
(30, '2013-09-07 02:08:18', 'Bria Slaughter', 'princessbri2@yahoo.com', '', '', 'Blackbarbiedoll504', 0, 'ex_t2,ex_t3', '', '', '', '', 'I want to build my web developing skills, because its my passion. I also want to show that women can be involved in technology!', 'I heard about you on Google.com', '', '', 0, 0, 0);

